Privacy Policy
We will not sell, rent, share, or disclose personally identifiable information from customers for commercial purposes.
Customers will receive proper notice when information about them might go to third parties, and customers will have an opportunity to choose not to share the information.
We will share customer information only as described below:
We partner with other companies for functions such as fulfilling, shipping, and processing credit card payments, and therefore we need to give them access to this information for them to perform these tasks. These partners have contractually agreed not to use this information for any other purposes.
In the event that Loog Guitars, LLC. is acquired, customer information will be one of the transferred assets.
We release account and other personal information when we are prompted to do so in order to comply with the law, or protect our company from fraud and credit crimes.
Users under 18 years old may shop at our website only with the involvement of a parent or guardian.
